==English==

===Noun phrase===
'''fanny pack'''
#A small pouch worn on the outside of clothing attached around the waist.
#:''She wears her '''fanny pack''' every day on her morning jog around Central Park.''

===Usage note===
*In [[Britain]] this is called a [[bum bag]] as [[fanny]] is a vulgarity.  In America, [[bum]] is either a harmless euphemism for the buttocks or a deragatory term for a homeless person; a hobo.